<subSubSection pageId="372" pageNumber="373" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="372" pageNumber="373">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="372" pageNumber="373">
This species has been known for a long time under the name 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1760" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="372" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ustulatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="372" pageNumber="373">Bembidion ustulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Linnaeus, 1758). Lindroth (1957b: 334-335) suggested to drop the name to promote stability. Four other subspecies of 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="372" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetracolum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="372" pageNumber="373">Bembidion tetracolum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are found in the Palaearctic Region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
